## Overview
The `web_search` workflow node provides first-class web search capability
directly in workflow DAGs. No need for raw HTTP — just specify provider,
query, and go.

## Supported Providers

| Provider | API Key Env Var   | Free Tier            | Notes                         |
|----------|-------------------|----------------------|-------------------------------|
| brave    | BRAVE_API_KEY     | 2,000 queries/month  | Privacy-focused, high quality |
| serper   | SERPER_API_KEY    | 2,500 queries        | Google results via API        |
| searxng  | (none needed)     | Unlimited (self-host)| Requires local SearXNG instance |

## Setup
Set your API key as an environment variable:
  export BRAVE_API_KEY=your_key_here
  export SERPER_API_KEY=your_key_here

Or pass directly in workflow parameters:
  {{"api_key": "your_key_here"}}

Or use expression interpolation:
  {{"api_key": "$env.BRAVE_API_KEY"}}

## Node Parameters

| Parameter | Type   | Default     | Description                                          |
|-----------|--------|-------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| provider  | string | brave       | Search provider: brave, searxng, serper              |
| query     | string | (required)  | Search query. Supports $input, $node expressions     |
| api_key   | string | (from env)  | API key. Falls back to env var per provider           |
| count     | int    | 10          | Number of results to return                          |
| freshness | string | (none)      | Time filter: day, week, month, year (brave/serper)   |
| language  | string | en          | Language code: en, es, de, fr, etc.                  |
| base_url  | string | localhost:8888 | SearXNG instance URL (searxng provider only)      |

## Output Format
{{
  "provider": "brave",
  "query": "transformers research 2026",
  "count": 5,
  "results": [
    {{"title": "...", "url": "...", "snippet": "...", "age": "2d"}},
    ...
  ],
  "elapsed_ms": 342
}}

